reviews.comments: Love this product.  I have been using it for years and it is silky soft and gives my skin a great feel.  It helps retain moisture and softness.

reviews.comments:
After I use up my last jar, I won't buy again.  The formula changed and not for the better.  It doesn't hydrate as much. reviews.headline: Caused blemishes
reviews.comments: I am 67 years old and my face is starting to feel dry and rough. I asked for a good moisturizer and this product was highly recommended by a sales associate. I felt it was a bit pricey but since it was so highly recommended I thought it was probably worth the cost. Unfortunately, this cream caused my skin to break out, which hasn't happened since I was a teenager. I didn't think my skin was sensitive but I guess its changing as I age. I cannot personally recommend this moisturizer.

reviews.headline: New formula is not good. Do not recommend. Just
reviews.comments: I used to love this cream before they came out with a new formula. The new formula does not feel as luxurious or thick and it burned my skin. My skin has been super red on the cheek area and forehead since using this product again and my skin has a burning sensation every time I use the product. It's no longer worth the price tag, i would recommend going with something else. The CocoKind moosturizer is much more affordable and feels a lot better on the skin.

reviews.headline: Great Hydrating Cream
reviews.comments: Have used this product for several years works very well keeps you face feeling smooth and keeps those lines out of your face in control.  I am over 64 years old, and have received compliments about my face complexion and  they can't believe it!

reviews.headline: Face breaks out!
reviews.comments: Was great at first but it give you a heavy sticky feeling after application which is weird. Usually good creams don't give you that tacky feeling and they absorb right into your pores. Then it clogs all my pores every time I use it and i get tiny bumps everywhere. I wouldn't recommend.

reviews.headline: I Am Hooked
reviews.comments: I tried a travel size of Confidence in a Cream to see how it reacts to my mature skin. I'm happy it is moisturizer that is gentle in my skin and I'm seeing a softer skin. Chrissy was my tech and she was amazing and quite knowledgeable about skin - even mature skin like mine. She picked out each type of makeup I was looking for and I'm looking forward to revisiting her and purchasing additional products she recommends. I'll be back to buy a full size Confidence in a Cream Anti-Aging Hydrating Moisturizer by IT Cosmetics.

reviews.headline: Feels like luxury
reviews.comments: I love this moisturizer for am/pm usage. The formula is rich without feeling oily. I have somewhat mature (40yo), dry skin. This product also does well under makeup.

faceoff_positive.comments: I always deal with dry patches that ruin my makeup and I have very sensitive skin, anything can give me redness. I had samples of the old formula. It felt a little greasy once applied, but calmed my dry skin so much. After every use when I would wake up, my skin was so smooth and firm as if I've had botox which I am against and would never do (33 yrs old). I had the best results when I applied it after a sebum removal cleansing. It made my skin look plump as if it regained its elasticity. The name confidence in a cream was suitable! I have been impressed by serums but never really with a moisturizer. I used it in combination with a retinol serum which is good by itself, though this cream truly made a difference for me. Under makeup it also created a nice hydrated base, no dry patches. The new formula is harder to work with. I also loved the scent and texture of the old formula. The new one does not glide and does not spread easy, it is VERY very thick. The old one was such a joy to apply, I was looking forward to do my skin care routine. 4 stars because the new formula has about the same effect on my skin, but it doesn't apply nicely. It feels heavy. Old formula did not cause me breakouts, white heads or black heads. New one feels heavy, have not seen any breakouts yet though. Would not use the new one under makeup unless I mix it with a HA serum to make it less thick. My photo is my results using the old one.
faceoff_positive.headline: It was an AMAZING cream. New formula is so and so.

faceoff_negative.comments:
I am almost 65 years old, and I am reviewing the "Confidence In A Cream" Anti-Aging Hydrating Moisturizer". I just now received my first shipment of IT Cosmetics products. I decided to start with the basic moisturizer, this one. I find it to be not worthy to be called a " moisturizer" as it was dry feeling once it dried down on my skin. I use VERY good, high end skincare and have for all my adult life. I am a former model, so perfect skin is the NORM for me, not the exception.

I DO UNDERSTAND why people are complaining, although I have 0 experience with the previous formula to compare. This is a totally inferior " cream" that I had to get out of the jar with a disposable makeup spatula. It was very firm, not at all gliding or moisturizing when I applied it with clean fingers and spread it around. 
Maybe L'Oreal needed to make these changes for economic reasons, but I think you are going to lose support for this product with your customer base to the point that it will fail. 

OTOH, the " Confidence In A Night Cream" is WONDERFUL and is what I will be using from now on, day and night. I think you really took all the good stuff and put it into the Night Cream. I would put it against my favorite night cream any day, and the other brand is priced higher and is European- made. 

I think you need to work off your night cream, which is likely for more mature skin, and have a multi-purpose day cream for more mature and dry skin types, like mine. I will not be rebuying this for any reason unless you reformulate your reformulation to be truly full of hydrating and absorbable ingredients. I should not have to put facial oil and serum on my face in the AM to get enough " Slip" to use " Confidence In A Cream" without pulling on my skin. 
Again, without the history of other users, I consider this to be less than drugstore effective as a humectant and a failure in providing or retaining any moisture in human skin.
faceoff_negative.headline: First and Last Purchase Of Item- It IS a Failure!
